<h4 id="definition">Definition</h4>
<ol>
  <li>An association is any link between as systemâ€™s input and output such that
when a pattern A is presented to the system it will respond with patter B.
When two patterns are linked by an association, the input pattern is often
referred to as the stimulus, likewise, the output pattern is refereed to as
the response.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="instar-and-outstar">Instar and Outstar</h4>
<ol>
  <li>The instar is a network that is trained to recognize a pattern.</li>
  <li>The outstar  is a network that is trained to recall a pattern.</li>
</ol>

